    "what_description": "Stevia eupatoria is a perennial herb native to the Iberian Peninsula, belonging to the family Asteraceae. It grows to 60-100 cm in height, with a woody base and a leafy stem bearing ovate or lanceolate leaves 2-10 cm in length and 1-4 cm in width. The leaves are alternate, simple, and entire, with a pubescent underside. Stevia eupatoria produces small white or yellowish flowers in a capitulum, with a daisy-like appearance, from June to September. The plant prefers well-drained soils and full sun to partial shade.",
