    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Stevia eupatoria are multifaceted, exhibiting significant antioxidant activity, thanks to the presence of flavonoids and phenolic acids that neutralize free radicals and protect cells from oxidative damage. Additionally, the antimicrobial properties of Stevia eupatoria are attributed to its bioactive compounds, including saponins and volatile oils, which inhibit the growth of various microorganisms and combat infections. Stevia eupatoria also possesses potent anti-inflammatory properties, mediated by sesquiterpene lactones that reduce inflammation and alleviate pain. Furthermore, the cardioprotective effects of Stevia eupatoria are attributed to the presence of flavonoids and terpenoids, which lower blood pressure, reduce lipid peroxidation, and prevent cardiovascular diseases. Notably, Stevia eupatoria has been found to exhibit antidiabetic properties, with compounds like steviol and rebaudioside A being used to improve glucose metabolism and reduce insulin resistance.",
