    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Stevia eupatoria are rebaudioside A, steviol, rebaudioside C, stevioside, and dulcoside A. Rebaudioside A is a glycoside responsible for the sweetness of Stevia and has been shown to exhibit antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties. Steviol is a compound that is converted to stevioside, a potent antioxidant and anti-inflammatory, which may help to reduce inflammation and oxidative stress. Rebaudioside C is another glycoside that has been found to have antioxidant and anti-inflammatory activities, suggesting it may contribute to the plant's potential health benefits. Dulcoside A, a minor constituent, has been reported to possess anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties, although its role in the plant's healing effects is less well-documented.",
