    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Stevia eupatoria are derived from its leaves, which contain bioactive compounds such as stevioside and rebaudioside. Infusion and decoction are prepared by steeping the leaves in hot water to extract these compounds, which can be used to treat various health conditions, including diabetes and hypertension. Tincture is made by soaking the leaves in a solvent such as ethanol or glycerin to create a concentrated extract, which can be used topically or internally. Tea is prepared similarly to infusion but is typically made with a smaller amount of leaves and is often used as a calming agent. A salve is prepared by infusing the leaves in a carrier oil such as coconut or olive oil, which can be used topically to treat skin conditions.",
